JWT AUTHENTICATION - POINT TO POINT NOTES
=========================================

PART 1: REGISTER FLOW
---------------------
- Client POST request bhejta hai /user/register endpoint par.
- Request body mein username aur password hota hai.
- Request UserController.register() method tak pahunchti hai.
- Controller MyUserDetailsService.createUser(user) method call karta hai.
- createUser() method ke andar:
    - Pehle BCryptPasswordEncoder(12) se password encode hota hai.
    - user.setPassword(encodedPassword) se user object mein encoded password set hota hai.
    - userRepository.save(user) call hota hai.
- UserRepository JPA ka method use karke MySQL database mein INSERT query run karta hai.
- Database mein naya user save ho jata hai.
- Saved user object (with ID) controller ko return hota hai.
- Controller client ko saved user object JSON format mein return karta hai.
- Response Status: 200 OK.


PART 2: LOGIN FLOW
------------------
- Client POST request bhejta hai /user/login endpoint par.
- Request body mein UserDTO object hota hai jisme username aur password hai.
- Request UserController.login() method tak pahunchti hai.
- Controller sabse pehle AuthenticationManager.authenticate() call karta hai.
- authenticate() ke parameter mein UsernamePasswordAuthenticationToken object pass hota hai.
- AuthenticationManager internally MyUserDetailsService.loadUserByUsername() call karta hai.
- loadUserByUsername() method:
    - userRepository.findByUsername(username) call karta hai.
    - Database se SELECT * FROM Users WHERE username = ? query run hoti hai.
    - Agar user nahi milta toh UsernameNotFoundException throw hota hai.
    - Agar user milta hai toh UserPrincipal object return hota hai.
- AuthenticationManager received password ko database ke encoded password se match karta hai (BCrypt compare).
- Agar password match ho jata hai toh Authentication object return hota hai.
- Agar password match nahi hota toh BadCredentialsException throw hota hai.
- Authentication success hone par controller SecurityContextHolder.getContext().setAuthentication() call karta hai.
- Is call se current user us request ke liye "Logged In" mark ho jata hai.
- Controller phir user ke roles extract karta hai authentication.getAuthorities() se.
- Roles ki list ["ROLE_SELLER"] format mein milti hai.
- Controller phir se userDetailsService.loadUserByUsername() call karta hai UserDetails object lene ke liye.
- Controller JwtUtil.generateToken(username, roles) call karta hai.
- generateToken() method:
    - Token ka Header banata hai: {"alg":"HS256","typ":"JWT"}
    - Token ka Payload banata hai: {"sub":"rahul","roles":["ROLE_SELLER"],"iat":timestamp,"exp":timestamp+2min}
    - Secret Key se Signature generate karta hai.
    - Teen parts ko . se join karke ek String token banata hai.
- Generated token String controller ko return hota hai.
- Controller client ko token String return karta hai.
- Response Status: 200 OK.
- Response Body: Token String (eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJzdWIiOi...)


PART 3: PROTECTED API CALL FLOW (WITH JWT TOKEN)
------------------------------------------------
- Client kisi protected endpoint par request bhejta hai, example: GET /api/products.
- Request ke Header mein Authorization: Bearer <token> include hota hai.
- Request sabse pehle JwtRequestFilter.doFilterInternal() method mein jaati hai.
- Filter Authorization header ko extract karta hai: String authHeader = request.getHeader("Authorization").
- Filter check karta hai ki header null toh nahi aur Bearer  se start hota hai ya nahi.
- Agar header valid hai toh authHeader.substring(7) se token extract karta hai.
- Filter phir jwtUtil.extractUsername(token) call karta hai.
- IMPORTANT: Extract hua username username variable mein assign karna zaroori hai: username = jwtUtil.extractUsername(token).
- extractUsername() token ke Payload se sub claim nikalta hai.
- Agar username != null aur SecurityContext mein pehle se authentication nahi hai toh filter aage badhta hai.
- Filter userDetailsService.loadUserByUsername(username) call karta hai.
- Ye call database se user ki details load karta hai.
- Filter phir jwtUtil.extractRole(token) call karta hai roles nikalne ke liye.
- Roles ki list ko List<SimpleGrantedAuthority> mein convert karta hai.
- Filter jwtUtil.validToken(token, userDetails.getUsername()) call karta hai.
- validToken() check karta hai:
    - Token ka username match karta hai ya nahi.
    - Token expire hua hai ya nahi (isTokenExpired()).
- Agar token valid hai toh filter UsernamePasswordAuthenticationToken object banata hai.
- authToken.setDetails(new WebAuthenticationDetailsSource().buildDetails(request)) call karta hai.
- Filter SecurityContextHolder.getContext().setAuthentication(authToken) call karta hai.
- Is call se user Spring Security ke context mein authenticated set ho jata hai.
- Filter ant mein filterChain.doFilter(request, response) call karta hai.
- Request aage badhkar DispatcherServlet tak pahunchti hai.
- DispatcherServlet request ko appropriate Controller ke method par route karta hai.
- Controller ka method (e.g., ProductController.getAllProducts()) execute hota hai.
- Controller business logic run karta hai aur response object return karta hai.
- Response client ko JSON format mein milta hai.
- Response Status: 200 OK.
- Response Body: ["Mobile", "Laptop", "TV", "Fridge", "AC"]


PART 4: IMPORTANT POINTS (YAAD RAKHNE LAYAK)
--------------------------------------------
- BCryptPasswordEncoder(12) - 12 rounds ka password hashing.
- UserDetailsService - Interface, database se user load karne ke liye.
- UserDetails - Interface, Spring Security ka user representation.
- UserPrincipal - Custom class jo UserDetails implement karta hai.
- OncePerRequestFilter - Har request par ek baar execute hota hai.
- SecurityContextHolder - Current logged-in user ka context store karta hai.
- AuthenticationManager - Authentication process ka main manager.
- DaoAuthenticationProvider - Database authentication ke liye provider.
- SessionCreationPolicy.STATELESS - Server session create nahi karta.
- JWT Token 3 parts mein divide hota hai: Header.Payload.Signature.
- Token expiry tumne 1000 * 60 * 2 (2 minutes) set kiya hai.
- Har application restart par nayi secret key generate hoti hai (current code mein).
- /user/register aur /user/login public endpoints hain.
- GET /api/** bhi public hai (tumhari config mein).
- Baaki sab endpoints authenticated hain.


PART 5: COMMON MISTAKE (FORBIDDEN 403 KA REASON)
------------------------------------------------
- Galat Line: jwtUtil.extractUsername(token);
- Sahi Line: username = jwtUtil.extractUsername(token);
- Agar username = nahi likhoge toh username variable null rahega.
- Null hone ki wajah se if (username != null) block skip ho jaayega.
- SecurityContext set nahi hoga.
- Controller tak pahunchne se pehle Spring Security 403 Forbidden throw kar dega.


PART 6: JWT TOKEN STRUCTURE
---------------------------
- Header: Algorithm aur Token Type batata hai. (HS256, JWT)
- Payload: User data aur claims store karta hai. (username, roles, expiry)
- Signature: Header aur Payload ko secret key se hash karta hai. (Tampering detect karne ke liye)
- Format: Header.Payload.Signature (Base64 encoded strings joined by dot)


PART 7: SECURITY CONFIG KEY POINTS
----------------------------------
- .csrf(csrf -> csrf.disable()) : CSRF protection disable kiya kyunki JWT stateless hai.
- .authorizeHttpRequests() : URL based security rules define karta hai.
- .requestMatchers("/user/register", "/user/login").permitAll() : Ye URLs public hain.
- .anyRequest().authenticated() : Baaki sab URLs require authentication.
- .sessionManagement(session -> session.sessionCreationPolicy(SessionCreationPolicy.STATELESS)) : Session create nahi hoti.
- .authenticationProvider(authenticationProvider()) : Custom auth provider set kiya.
- .addFilterBefore(jwtRequestFilter, UsernamePasswordAuthenticationFilter.class) : JWT filter add kiya.


PART 8: JWT UTIL KEY METHODS
----------------------------
- generateToken(username, roles) : Token create karta hai.
- extractUsername(token) : Token se username nikalta hai.
- extractRole(token) : Token se roles nikalta hai.
- extractExpiration(token) : Token se expiry date nikalta hai.
- isTokenExpired(token) : Check karta hai token expire hua ya nahi.
- validToken(token, username) : Token valid hai ya nahi (username match + not expired).
- getSignedKey() : Secret key ko Signing Key mein convert karta hai.

