JWT AUTHENTICATION - SHORT NOTES
================================

1. UserController
-----------------
- /user/register -> User save karta hai DB mein (password encoded)
- /user/login -> Username/password verify karta hai, JWT token return karta hai


2. UserDTO
----------
- Login request ke liye DTO
- Fields: username, password


3. User (Entity)
----------------
- Database table: Users
- Fields: id (auto), username, password


4. UserRepository
-----------------
- JpaRepository extend karta hai
- Custom method: findByUsername(username)


5. JwtUtil
----------
- generateToken() -> Token banata hai (Header + Payload + Signature)
- extractUsername() -> Token se username nikalta hai
- extractRole() -> Token se roles nikalta hai
- validToken() -> Token sahi hai ya nahi check karta hai
- Token expiry: 2 minutes (1000*60*2)


6. JwtRequestFilter
-------------------
- OncePerRequestFilter extend karta hai
- Har request ka Authorization header check karta hai
- Token valid hai toh SecurityContext set karta hai
- ⚠️ Common Mistake: username = jwtUtil.extractUsername(token)  // 'username =' bhoolna mat


7. SecurityConfig
-----------------
- @EnableWebSecurity + @EnableMethodSecurity
- Public URLs: /user/register, /user/login, GET /api/**
- Session: STATELESS (JWT ke liye zaroori)
- AuthenticationProvider: DaoAuthenticationProvider (DB se verify karta hai)
- PasswordEncoder: BCryptPasswordEncoder
- JwtRequestFilter add kiya UsernamePasswordAuthenticationFilter se pehle


8. UserPrincipal
----------------
- UserDetails interface implement karta hai
- User entity ko Spring Security UserDetails mein convert karta hai
- getAuthorities() -> ROLE_SELLER return karta hai


9. MyUserDetailsService
-----------------------
- UserDetailsService implement karta hai
- createUser() -> Password encode karke user save karta hai
- loadUserByUsername() -> DB se user load karta hai, UserPrincipal return karta hai


10. JWT Token Structure
-----------------------
- Header: {"alg":"HS256","typ":"JWT"}
- Payload: {"sub":"username","roles":["ROLE_SELLER"],"iat":time,"exp":time+2min}
- Signature: HMACSHA256(Header.Payload, secretKey)
- Format: xxxxx.yyyyy.zzzzz


11. Flow Summary
----------------
Register: POST /user/register -> Password encode -> DB save
Login: POST /user/login -> Verify user -> Generate Token -> Return Token
API Call: Header Bearer Token -> Filter validate -> SecurityContext set -> Controller execute


12. Important Points
--------------------
- BCryptPasswordEncoder(12) -> 12 rounds hashing
- SessionCreationPolicy.STATELESS -> No session created
- OncePerRequestFilter -> Every request intercepted once
- SecurityContextHolder -> Stores authenticated user
- AuthenticationManager -> Manages authentication process